Description: Handle sliver of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium, very micaceous, red-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Zenon. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1328)
